  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package intentionally references the hemolysis power-law calibration dataset described in Faghih & Sharp (2019) as extended by the 2024 methods article indexed at https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003; that identifier is cited as a referencesIdentifier but no corresponding typed node is declared within this package graph, constituting the W-CON-02 dangling-reference condition under test.",
