    "rationale": "Despite all seven assessed credibility factors falling below required levels and six factors flagged as epistemic gaps, the assessment team accepted the package for submission under a risk-mitigation agreement requiring post-market hemolysis surveillance and a committed remediation plan for model-form uncertainty quantification. The hemolysis power-law calibration methodology referenced in the 2024 methods article (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) was cited as foundational justification for the power-law constant selection; however, that reference is not resolved within this package and no external fetch hint is provided, leaving the identifier dangling within the local graph.",
